article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- — Kobe Stewart had 26 points in Presbyterian's 71-68 win over Wofford on Wednesday night. Stewart added 10 rebounds for the Blue Hose (2-2). Carl Parrish scored 11 points, shooting 4 for 10, including 1 for 4 from beyond the arc. Kory Mincy shot 3 for 11 (1 for 6 from 3-point range) and 3 of 4 from the free-throw line to finish with 10 points. The Terriers (1-2) were led by Corey Tripp, who recorded 15 points and six assists. Jackson Sivills added 13 points for Wofford. Jeremy Lorenz also had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
